text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia durabilis is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to an area along the south coast in the Goldfields-Esperance and Great Southern regions of Western Australia.The slender, open and spinescent shrub typically grows to a height of 0.7 to 2.0 metres (2 to 7 ft). It blooms from October to April and produces cream-yellow flowers.
